{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01W14KziuLyWGjJoDSDFJhan","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture:\n- 3-node `es-cluster` with master, data, and ingest roles\n- `app-data` index has 1 primary shard on `es-cluster-1` and 1 replica on `es-cluster-2`\n- Cluster is currently green\n\nMy plan:\n1. **Add allocation attributes to existing nodes**: Update the `es-config` ConfigMap to add `node.attr.zone: original` to the existing nodes\n2. **Create 2 new data nodes** as a new StatefulSet with `node.attr.zone: new` attribute\n3. **Configure these new nodes to join the existing cluster** (using the same cluster name and seed hosts)\n4. **Set routing allocation** on the `app-data` index to prefer the new nodes\n\nI need to be careful here—restarting the existing nodes to update their ConfigMap would disrupt the cluster. Instead, I'll keep the 3-node `es-cluster` StatefulSet unchanged and create a separate StatefulSet for the 2 new data nodes. Both will join the same Elasticsearch cluster, but I'll use different ConfigMaps to assign them different allocation attributes: `node.attr.zone: original` for the existing nodes and `node.attr.zone: new` for the new ones.\n\nThe sequence is: first spin up the 2 new nodes with their zone attribute so they join the cluster, then update the existing nodes' ConfigMap and perform a rolling restart to add their zone attribute, and finally configure the `app-data` index routing to target the new nodes. I'm also thinking through what verification checks I need to confirm everything is working correctly.\n\nNow I'm designing the new StatefulSet for the data nodes—it needs to reference the same cluster name, point to the existing master nodes for discovery, have data-only roles, and carry the `zone: new` attribute, while the original nodes get updated with `zone: original`.\n\nThe tricky part is the rolling restart of the existing nodes—with 3 nodes and only 1 primary shard, I need to be careful about availability during the update.\n\nI'm settling on this sequence: first spin up the new data nodes with the `zone: new` attribute so they join the cluster, then update the routing policy on `app-data` to prefer the new zone, which will trigger shard migration. Once that's done, I can safely do a rolling restart of the existing nodes to add their `zone: original` attribute without disrupting the cluster.\n\nNow I'm creating the ConfigMap for the new nodes, setting up the cluster discovery and node attributes...\n\nFor the existing nodes, I need to add the `node.attr.zone: original` attribute to their configuration so they can be distinguished from the new nodes during the migration.\n\nNow I'm thinking through the architecture for the new data nodes—they'll need their own headless service for transport communication, a separate ConfigMap, and a StatefulSet with 2 replicas. The key consideration is that `cluster.initial_master_nodes` shouldn't be in the new nodes' config since the cluster is already bootstrapped and this parameter is only for initial cluster formation. I'll skip including `cluster.initial_master_nodes` in the new nodes' configuration to keep it clean, then move on to writing out all the Kubernetes manifests.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":519,"cache_read_input_tokens":37449,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":519},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"27a39412-d024-4cbc-9421-608229275cd9","uuid":"ce0dbad4-03ef-4207-91ce-79ef9e3619b2","request_id":"req_011CcMeid6tZBNTmPSp1ErrB"}
